 synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert De Haggerston I was born about 1313, in Haggerston, Durham, England, United Kingdom. She married Robert De Haggerston I about 1335. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"abt. 1313–":"umbes 1313–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1335–1399":"1335–1399","1337–Male":"1337–Surnud","1313–Female":"1313–Surnud","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","abt 1337":"umbes 1337","1313":"1313","abt. 1313":"umbes 1313","1399":"1399","1310":"1310","about 1335":"umbes 1335","of Haggerston in Islandshire, Durham, Engl.":"Haggerston, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Haggerston in Islandshire, Durham, England":"Haggerston, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England"},"fi":{"abt. 1313–":"noin 1313–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1335–1399":"1335–1399","1337–Male":"1337–Kuollut","1313–Female":"1313–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","abt 1337":"noin 1337","1313":"1313","abt. 1313":"noin 1313","1399":"1399","1310":"1310","about 1335":"noin 1335","of Haggerston in Islandshire, Durham, Engl.":"Haggerston, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Haggerston in Islandshire, Durham, England":"Haggerston, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England"},"fr":{"abt. 1313–":"